		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've never used Common Lisp, but I took two quarters of Scheme in college. (<a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=52930#52930" class="postlink">What else did I do with Scheme?</a>) My Python shows some of the influence of Scheme; I'm more likely to use list comprehensions like [expr for x in ls if condition] which is a lot like what Lisp-style languages call "map" and "filter".

		

